    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text means — moving from observation to discerning the narrator's theological intent in its original covenantal context. The movements below trace the chapter's argument from the domestic failure that triggers the crisis through the sovereign permission that ends it. Orthodox commentators disagree on the precise relationship between God's permissive will and the institution of monarchy; both positions are represented below. Where Hebrew vocabulary sharpens the English, a brief note follows each movement.",
